            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:400;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;margin-bottom:12px;">Taranis Market Sentiment ended the month of <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">June 2026 with a net performance of -6.4%.</span></div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;margin-bottom:12px;">The systematic strategy <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">fell in line with the S&amp;P, while our tech long/short</span> dropped double digits but remains up over <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">50% YTD</span>.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;margin-bottom:12px;">The central event was the <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">US government temporarily</span> forcing <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">Anthropic</span> to pull its Claude Mythos 5 and Fable 5 models offline for around three weeks. We see this as a <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">short-term disruption</span> rather than a lasting slowdown in the AI race.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;margin-bottom:12px;"><span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">Volatility</span> reached extreme levels, with <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">SOX realized volatility hitting 70%</span>, a <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">(-4.8%)</span> Nasdaq day in early June and a <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">(-7%)</span> intra-month drawdown.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;margin-bottom:12px;">We exited most of our <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">US space holdings</span>, kept <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">European names</span> and began adding <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">Asian ones</span>, cutting roughly a <span style="font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;">third of our space long exposure</span> while adding to shorts. Ahead of July earnings, we will adjust our positioning around valuation and growth.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.5;text-align:left;">Please, find our Taranis Market Sentiment monthly report for June 2026 by <a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/10JI0ortNBuKW_03SRqlqUC3QRtgao_iV/view?usp=sharing" style="color:#0066cc;text-decoration:underline;">clicking here</a>.</div>

